1. Variable 'approx_health_factor' failed the non-proportional test: p-value is 0.0005.

   Advice 1: the functional form of the variable 'approx_health_factor' might be incorrect. That is,
there may be non-linear terms missing. The proportional hazard test used is very sensitive to
incorrect functional forms. See documentation in link [D] below on how to specify a functional form.

   Advice 2: try binning the variable 'approx_health_factor' using pd.cut, and then specify it in
`strata=['approx_health_factor', ...]` in the call in `.fit`. See documentation in link [B] below.

